# Pipeline And Runtime Patterns

- Node runtime config belongs in `lib/runtime-config.cjs`.
- Firebase Admin belongs in `lib/firebase-admin.cjs`.
- Scanner config belongs in `scanner/lib/config.js`.
- Python config belongs in `pipeline/config_loader.py`.
- Add config keys to `.env.example` and `scripts/setup-github-actions-config.sh` together.
- Fail with missing key names only. Never print values.
- Do not read or write legacy JSON credentials/config files.
- Keep scripts repo-relative and cross-platform where practical.
- Keep generated outputs under ignored paths.

Checks:

```bash
bash -n scripts/*.sh scripts/scanner/*.sh scanner/yahoo-svc/start.sh
node --check path/to/file.js
python -m py_compile path/to/file.py
node scripts/scan-sensitive-candidates.cjs --all
```
